data.name: ArgumentIsEmpty
data.value: The string argument '{argumentName}' cannot be empty.

data.name: CircularDependency
data.value: A circular model foreign key dependency was detected: {cycle}.

data.name: InvalidEnumValue
data.value: The value provided for argument '{argumentName}' must be a valid value of enum type '{enumType}'.

data.name: InvalidPropertiesExpression
data.value: The properties expression '{expression}' is not valid. The expression should represent a property access: 't => t.MyProperty'. When specifying multiple properties use an anonymous type: 't => new {{ t.MyProperty1, t.MyProperty2 }}'.

data.name: InvalidPropertyExpression
data.value: The expression '{expression}' is not a valid property expression. The expression should represent a property access: 't => t.MyProperty'.

data.name: IdentityConflict
data.value: The instance of entity type '{entityType}' cannot be tracked because another instance of this type with the same key is already being tracked. For new entities consider using an IIdentityGenerator to generate unique key values.

data.name: NullPrimaryKey
data.value: The instance of entity type '{entityType}' cannot be tracked because it has a null primary key. Either set the key explicitly or consider using an IValueGenerator to generate unique key values.

data.name: WrongStateManager
data.value: Cannot start tracking StateEntry for entity type '{entityType}' because it was created by a different StateManager instance.

data.name: MultipleStateEntries
data.value: Cannot start tracking StateEntry for entity type '{entityType}' because another StateEntry is already tracking the same entity.

data.name: EntityTypeNotFound
data.value: The entity type '{entityType}' was not found. Ensure that the entity type '{entityType}' has been added to the model.

data.name: PropertyNotFound
data.value: The property '{property}' on entity type '{entityType}' could not be found. Ensure that the property exists and has been included in the model.

data.name: EmptySequence
data.value: Sequence contains no elements.

data.name: MoreThanOneElement
data.value: Sequence contains more than one element.

data.name: MoreThanOneMatch
data.value: Sequence contains more than one matching element.

data.name: NoMatch
data.value: Sequence contains no matching element.

data.name: CollectionArgumentIsEmpty
data.value: The collection argument '{argumentName}' must contain at least one element.

data.name: InconsistentEntityType
data.value: The properties provided for the argument '{argumentName}' are declared on different entity types.

data.name: EntityRequiresKey
data.value: The entity type '{entityType}' requires a key to be defined.

data.name: KeyPropertiesWrongEntity
data.value: The specified key properties are not declared on the entity type '{entityType}'. Ensure key properties are declared on the target entity type.

data.name: ForeignKeyPropertiesWrongEntity
data.value: The specified foreign key properties are not declared on the entity type '{entityType}'. Ensure foreign key properties are declared on the target entity type.

data.name: IndexPropertiesWrongEntity
data.value: The specified index properties are not declared on the entity type '{entityType}'. Ensure index properties are declared on the target entity type.

data.name: IQueryableNotAsync
data.value: The source IQueryable doesn't implement IAsyncEnumerable<{genericParameter}>. Only sources that implement IAsyncEnumerable can be used for Entity Framework asynchronous operations.

data.name: IQueryableProviderNotAsync
data.value: The provider for the source IQueryable doesn't implement IAsyncQueryProvider. Only providers that implement IEntityQueryProvider can be used for Entity Framework asynchronous operations.

data.name: EagerOriginalValuesRequired
data.value: Lazy original value tracking cannot be turned on for entity type '{entityType}'. Entities that do not implement both INotifyPropertyChanging and INotifyPropertyChanged require original values to be stored eagerly in order to correct detect changes made to entities.

data.name: OriginalValueNotTracked
data.value: The original value for property '{property}' of entity type '{entityType}' cannot be accessed because it is not being tracked. To access all original values set 'UseLazyOriginalValues' to false on the entity type.

data.name: MissingBackingField
data.value: The property '{entityType}.{property}' is annotated with backing field '{field}' but that field cannot be found.

data.name: BadBackingFieldType
data.value: The annotated backing field '{field}' of type '{fieldType}' cannot be used for the property '{entityType}.{property}' of type '{propertyType}'. Only backing fields of types that are assignable from the property type can be used.

data.name: NoFieldOrSetter
data.value: No backing field could be discovered for property '{entityType}.{property}' and the property does not have a setter. Either use a backing field name that can be matched by convention, annotate the property with a backing field, or define a property setter.

data.name: NoClrType
data.value: The CLR entity materializer cannot be used for entity type '{entityType}' because it is a shadow-state entity type. Materialization to a CLR type is only possible for entity types that have a corresponding CLR type.

data.name: MultipleDataStoresConfigured
data.value: The data stores {storeNames}are configured. A context can only be configured to use a single data store.

data.name: NoDataStoreConfigured
data.value: No data stores are configured. Configure a data store using OnConfiguring or by creating an ImmutableDbContextOptions with a data store configured and passing it to the context.

data.name: NoDataStoreService
data.value: No data stores are available. Ensure that data store services are added inside the call to AddEntityFramework on your ServiceCollection.

data.name: MultipleDataStoresAvailable
data.value: The data stores {storeNames}are available. A context can only be configured to use a single data store. Configure a data store using OnConfiguring or by creating an ImmutableDbContextOptions with a data store configured and passing it to the context.

data.name: EntityConfigurationLocked
data.value: Cannot change the ImmutableDbContextOptions by calling '{memberName}' because it is locked. Use ImmutableDbContextOptionsBuilder to create ImmutableDbContextOptionss.

data.name: MultiplePropertiesMatchedAsKeys
data.value: Multiple potential primary key properties named '{property}' but differing only by case were found on entity type '{entityType}'. Configure the primary key explicitly using the SetKey fluent API.

data.name: NoValueGenerator
data.value: No {generator} value generator has been configured for property '{entityType}.{propertyName}'. To use value generation for properties of type '{propertyType}' the data store must configure an appropriate value generator.

data.name: PropertyWithStorageNameNotFound
data.value: A property with the storage name '{property}' on entity type '{entityType}' could not be found. Ensure that the property exists, has been included in the model, and has been configured with storage name specified.

data.name: CurrentValuesAlwaysInSync
data.value: CurrentValues are always in sync with the entity state.

data.name: DataStoreException
data.value: An error occured while running a data store operation. See InnerException for details.

data.name: LogExceptionDuringQueryIteration
data.value: An exception occurred in the data store while iterating the results of a query.

data.name: LogExceptionDuringSaveChanges
data.value: An exception occurred in the data store while saving changes.

data.name: PropertyExtensionInvoked
data.value: The Property<T> extension method may only be used within LINQ queries.

data.name: PropertyAlreadyOwned
data.value: The property '{property}' cannot be added to the entity type '{entityType}' because it already belongs to entity type '{existingEntityType}'.

data.name: DuplicateProperty
data.value: The property '{property}' cannot be added to the entity type '{entityType}' because an existing property with the same name already exists.

data.name: NoClrProperty
data.value: The property '{property}' cannot exist on entity type '{entityType}' because the property is not marked as shadow state and no corresponding CLR property exists on the underlying type.

data.name: WrongClrPropertyType
data.value: The property '{property}' cannot exist on entity type '{entityType}' because the property is not marked as shadow state and the type of the corresponding CLR property does not match the type specified in the property.

data.name: ClrPropertyOnShadowEntity
data.value: The property '{property}' cannot exist on entity type '{entityType}' because the entity type is marked as shadow state while the property is not. Shadow state entity types can only contain shadow state properties.

data.name: PropertyInUse
data.value: The property '{property}' cannot be removed from entity type '{entityType}' because it is being used in an index or key. All indexes and keys must be removed or redefined before the property can be removed.

data.name: KeyInUse
data.value: Cannot remove key from entity type '{entityType}' because it is referenced by a foreign key in entity type '{dependentType}'. All foreign keys must be removed or redefined before the referenced key can be removed.

data.name: ForeignKeyInUse
data.value: Cannot remove foreign key from entity type '{entityType}' because it is referenced by navigation property '{navigation}' in entity type '{dependentType}'. All navigations must be removed or redefined before the referenced foreign key can be removed.

data.name: NavigationAlreadyOwned
data.value: The navigation property '{navigation}' cannot be added to the entity type '{entityType}' because it already belongs to entity type '{existingEntityType}'.

data.name: DuplicateNavigation
data.value: The navigation property '{navigation}' cannot be added to the entity type '{entityType}' because an existing navigation property with the same name already exists.

data.name: NavigationOnShadowEntity
data.value: The navigation property '{navigation}' cannot be added to entity type '{entityType}' because the entity type is defined in shadow state and navigations properties cannot be added to shadow state.

data.name: NoClrNavigation
data.value: The navigation property '{navigation}' cannot be added to entity type '{entityType}' because there is no corresponding CLR property on the underlying type and navigations properties cannot be added to shadow state.

data.name: WrongClrSingleNavigationType
data.value: The navigation property '{navigation}' cannot be added to entity type '{entityType}' because its CLR type '{clrType}' does not match the CLR type '{targetType}' of the related entity.

data.name: WrongClrCollectionNavigationType
data.value: The collection navigation property '{navigation}' cannot be added to entity type '{entityType}' because its CLR type '{clrType}' does not implement 'IEnumerable<{targetType}>'. Collection navigation properties must implement IEnumerable<> of the related entity.

data.name: NavigationNotFound
data.value: The navigation property '{navigation}' on entity type '{entityType}' could not be found. Ensure that the navigation property exists and has been included in the model.

data.name: MultipleNavigations
data.value: The navigation properties '{navigation1}' and '{navigation2}' on entity type '{entityType}' are both backed by the same foreign key and point in the same direction. Each foreign key can have at most one navigation property and one inverse navigation property.

data.name: ForeignKeyCountMismatch
data.value: The number of properties specified for the foreign key on entity type '{dependentType}' does not match the number of properties in the referenced key on entity type '{principalType}'.

data.name: ForeignKeyTypeMismatch
data.value: The types of the properties specified for the foreign key on entity type '{dependentType}' do not match the types of the properties in the referenced key on entity type '{principalType}'.

data.name: NavigationBadType
data.value: The type of navigation property '{navigation}' on entity type '{entityType}' is '{foundType}' which does not implement ICollection<{targetType}>. Collection navigation properties must implement ICollection<> of the target type.

data.name: NavigationArray
data.value: The type of navigation property '{navigation}' on entity type '{entityType}' is '{foundType}' which is an array type.. Collection navigation properties cannot be arrays.

data.name: NavigationNoGetter
data.value: The navigation property '{navigation}' on entity type '{entityType}' does not have a getter.

data.name: NavigationNoSetter
data.value: The navigation property '{navigation}' on entity type '{entityType}' does not have a setter. Read-only collection navigation properties must be initialized before use.

data.name: NavigationCannotCreateType
data.value: The type of navigation property '{navigation}' on entity type '{entityType}' is '{foundType}' for which it was not possible to create a concrete instance. Either initialize the property before use, add a public parameterless constructor to the type, or use a type which can be assigned a HashSet<> or List<>.
